To find evidence-based treatments for monkeypox, researchers are drawing on lessons from the pandemic.  "One of the big changes we're seeing [is] randomized trials like this as part of an effective public health response" right from the beginning, said  @MartinLandray.

The plan: an estimated 500 patients with monkeypox will be randomized to either tecovirimat or placebo as part of the PLATINUM trial.   The main goal: to see if the drug reduces the number of days for the active lesions and ulcers to heal.   The hope: results before Christmas.

A study looking at antiviral tecovirimat, aka TPOXX, in patients with monkeypox is underway in the UK. It's led by the team behind the RECOVERY trial for COVID treatments.  "This is the first randomized controlled trial of treatments for monkeypox in the world," said @PeterHorby.
